### --- ADVANCED EXAMPLES ---
###

### ADVANCED 1: Reverse Dependency / Upstream Impact (GraphRAG wins, RAG fails)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/graphrag/upstream-impact?query=If we take the User Database offline for maintenance this weekend, which customer-facing services will break?
Accept: application/json

### ADVANCED 1: Standard RAG (Fails)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/rag/upstream-impact?query=If we take the User Database offline for maintenance this weekend, which customer-facing services will break?
Accept: application/json


### ADVANCED 2: Cross-Silo Aggregation (GraphRAG wins, RAG fails)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/graphrag/team-bottleneck?query=Which engineering team is currently responsible for the highest number of failing services?
Accept: application/json

### ADVANCED 2: Standard RAG (Fails)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/rag/team-bottleneck?query=Which engineering team is currently responsible for the highest number of failing services?
Accept: application/json


### ADVANCED 3: The Obscure Stack Trace (Standard RAG wins, GraphRAG fails)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/rag/obscure-trace?query=Have we ever seen a NullPointerException occurring exactly on line 428 in the old payment monolith?
Accept: application/json

### ADVANCED 3: GraphRAG (Success via Hybrid)
# It now successfully finds the obscure stack trace because we included the raw text in the Hybrid Graph traversal.
GET http://localhost:8080/api/graphrag/obscure-trace?query=Have we ever seen a NullPointerException occurring exactly on line 428 in the old payment monolith?
Accept: application/json

